prompt: "Modify the file `mcp_terminal/services/sandbox_policy.py`.\n\nOperation:\
  \ modify_file\n\n## Current state of the file\n\nThe file contains TrustCategory,\
  \ TrustBoundary, TERMINAL_TRUST_BOUNDARY,\nPolicyConfig, DEFAULT_POLICY_CONFIG,\
  \ ValidationResult, and SandboxPolicy\nwith a validate() method that checks project_id,\
  \ execution_kind, command/argv\nconsistency, cwd format, mode, network, image_profile,\
  \ and forbidden options.\n\n## MRS concept excerpt\n\nC-003 SandboxPolicy / C-010\
  \ ContainerRuntime mount modes:\n  - cwd must be relative and resolve inside /workspace\n\
  \  - Supported modes: read_only (default), workspace_write, scratch_write\n  - /workspace\
  \ is always the container mount point; caller cannot choose it\n  - Mount modes:\
  \ read_only (ro), workspace_write (rw), scratch_write (ro+scratch rw)\n\n## What\
  \ to add\n\nAdd the following @dataclass and method. Do not modify existing code.\n\
  \n### @dataclass(frozen=True) MountSpec  (add after DEFAULT_POLICY_CONFIG)\n\n```python\n\
  @dataclass(frozen=True)\nclass MountSpec:\n    \"\"\"Validated container mount configuration\
  \ produced by SandboxPolicy.\n\n    Consumed by ContainerRuntime (C-010) when creating\
  \ the container.\n    /workspace is always the mount point; callers cannot choose\
  \ it.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    workspace_source: Path\n    \"\"\"Verified canonical host\
  \ path of the project root to mount at /workspace.\"\"\"\n    workspace_readonly:\
  \ bool\n    \"\"\"True for read_only and scratch_write modes; False for workspace_write.\"\
  \"\"\n    scratch_enabled: bool\n    \"\"\"True for all modes (scratch tmpfs is\
  \ always provided).\"\"\"\n    workdir: str\n    \"\"\"Absolute container path for\
  \ working directory, e.g. /workspace/tests.\"\"\"\n    mode: str\n    \"\"\"Validated\
  \ mount mode string: read_only, workspace_write, or scratch_write.\"\"\"\n```\n\n\
  ### build_mount_spec() method on SandboxPolicy\n\nSignature:\n  def build_mount_spec(\n\
  \      self,\n      *,\n      workspace_source: Path,\n      mode: str,\n      cwd:\
  \ Optional[str],\n  ) -> tuple[Optional[MountSpec], Optional[ValidationResult]]:\n\
  \nDocstring:\n  \"\"\"Build a MountSpec from a validated mode and cwd.\n\n  Args:\n\
  \      workspace_source: Verified canonical host project root from\n          ProjectRegistry.resolve().\n\
  \      mode: Validated mode string (read_only, workspace_write, scratch_write).\n\
  \      cwd: Relative working directory within /workspace; None defaults to \".\"\
  .\n\n  Returns:\n      (MountSpec, None) on success, or (None, ValidationResult)\
  \ on failure.\n  \"\"\"\n\nImplementation:\n  safe_cwd = (cwd or \".\").strip()\n\
  \  if safe_cwd.startswith(\"/\") or \"..\" in safe_cwd:\n      return None, ValidationResult(\n\
  \          permitted=False,\n          error_code=\"INVALID_CWD\",\n          rejected_field=\"\
  cwd\",\n          detail=\"cwd must be relative and must not contain ..\",\n   \
  \   )\n  workdir = f\"/workspace/{safe_cwd}\".rstrip(\"/\") or \"/workspace\"\n\
  \  readonly = mode in (\"read_only\", \"scratch_write\")\n  return MountSpec(\n\
  \      workspace_source=workspace_source,\n      workspace_readonly=readonly,\n\
  \      scratch_enabled=True,\n      workdir=workdir,\n      mode=mode,\n  ), None\n\
  \n## Constraints\n- Do not remove or alter any existing code.\n- Insert MountSpec\
  \ after DEFAULT_POLICY_CONFIG constant.\n- Add build_mount_spec() to SandboxPolicy\
  \ class after the validate() method.\n- All type annotations required.\n- File must\
  \ not exceed 350 lines after this step.\n- Line length limit 99.\n"
